# Task 2 - Creating a Full System Backup Archive

## Problem Statement

After identifying the critical directories, the next objective was to create a compressed backup archive.

The backup needed to:

* include all critical directories
* use gzip compression
* be stored in the backups directory

---

# Command Used

```bash
tar -czvf backups/system-backup.tar.gz -T backup-list.txt
```

---

# Solution

```bash
labex:project/ $ tar -czvf backups/system-backup.tar.gz -T backup-list.txt
```

---

# Command Breakdown

| Option | Purpose                       |
| ------ | ----------------------------- |
| `-c`   | Create archive                |
| `-z`   | Compress using gzip           |
| `-v`   | Verbose output                |
| `-f`   | Specify archive filename      |
| `-T`   | Read backup targets from file |

---

# Example Output

```bash
config/
config/app.conf
data/
data/transactions.csv
logs/
logs/app.log
```

