# Task 5 - Scheduling Automated Backups

## Problem Statement

Manual backups are unreliable and prone to human error.

The objective was to automate backup creation using Linux cron scheduling.

Requirements included:

* execution every minute
* timestamped archive names
* compressed backups
* absolute file paths

---

# Command Used

```bash
crontab -e
```

---

# Cron Job Configuration

```bash
* * * * * tar -czf /home/labex/project/backups/backup-$(date +\%Y-\%m-\%d_\%H-\%M-\%S).tar.gz -C /home/labex/project data config logs
```

---

# Command Breakdown

| Component   | Purpose                           |
| ----------- | --------------------------------- |
| `* * * * *` | Run every minute                  |
| `tar -czf`  | Create compressed archive         |
| `date`      | Generate timestamp                |
| `-C`        | Change directory before archiving |

---

# Why This Matters

Automated backups provide:

* consistent protection
* reduced human error
* improved recovery readiness
* compliance support

Cron-based backup scheduling is frequently used for:

* application backups
* database exports
* server snapshots
* disaster recovery plans

